**Mission Briefing**

Our mission is to design and deploy a self-hosted GitLab/GitHub runner using Terraform, leveraging existing resources such as AWS, Azure, GCP, AWS SSM, managed onsite self-hosted, or containerized solutions like Docker, Kubernetes (k8s), virtual machines, or WebAssembly (WASM). We will also explore the theoretical foundations of our approach using lambda calculus and G√∂del numbers.

**Terraform Configuration**

To begin, we will create a Terraform configuration file (`main.tf`) that defines the infrastructure for our self-hosted runner. We will use the following providers:

* `aws` for AWS resources
* `azurerm` for Azure resources
* `google` for GCP resources
* `docker` for containerized solutions

** Self-Hosted Runner using AWS SSM**

We will create an AWS SSM (Systems Manager) document that defines the configuration for our self-hosted runner. This document will specify the instance type, operating system, and software requirements for the runner.

```terraform
# main.tf
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-west-2"
}

resource "aws_ssm_document" "self_hosted_runner" {
  name            = "Self-Hosted Runner"
  document_type = "Command"
  content        = jsonencode({
    schemaVersion = "1.2"
    description   = " Self-Hosted Runner"
    parameters    = {
      InstanceType = {
        type = "string"
        description = "Instance type for the runner"
        default     = "t2.micro"
      }
    }
    mainSteps = [
      {
        action = "aws:runInstance"
        name   = "Create Instance"
        inputs = {
          ImageId             = "ami-0c94855ba95c71c99"
          InstanceType       = "t2.micro"
          IamInstanceProfile = {
            name = "self-hosted-runner"
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  })
}
```

**Containerized Solution using Docker**

Alternatively, we can create a Docker container that runs the self-hosted runner.

```terraform
# main.tf
provider "docker" {
}

resource "docker_image" "self_hosted_runner" {
  name         = "self-hosted-runner"
  keep_locally = true
}

resource "docker_container" "self_hosted_runner" {
  name  = "self-hosted-runner"
  image = docker_image.self_hosted_runner.name
  ports {
    internal = 8080
    external = 8080
  }
}
```

**Kubernetes (k8s) Solution**

We can also deploy the self-hosted runner to a Kubernetes cluster.

```terraform
# main.tf
provider "kubernetes" {
  config_path = "~/.kube/config"
}

resource "kubernetes_deployment" "self_hosted_runner" {
  metadata {
    name = "self-hosted-runner"
  }
  spec {
    replicas = 1
    selector {
      match_labels = {
        app = "self-hosted-runner"
      }
    }
    template {
      metadata {
        labels = {
          app = "self-hosted-runner"
        }
      }
      spec {
        container {
          name  = "self-hosted-runner"
          image = "self-hosted-runner"
        }
      }
    }
